<h2>1. Policies</h2>

<h3>Introduction</h3>
<p>
As part of the process of making scientific and medical literature openly accessible on the Web, PLOS uses a streamlined production process that takes authors' submitted figures and tables straight to the formatting stage. PLOS does not provide graphics services. Although we provide guidelines and advice, <i>figure and table preparation is the author's responsibility.</i>
</p>

<p>
Please read the following guidelines carefully and thoroughly. Failure to comply with these guidelines can result in lower-quality published figures or inaccurate table layout, and/or prolonged publishing time of your article. 
</p>

<h3>Copyright and the Open Access Licenses</h3>
<p>
<i>Please do not submit any figures, photos, or tables that have been previously copyrighted unless you have and can supply written permission from the copyright holder to publish under the CC-BY or CC0 license.</i> </p>

<p>
Authors should read about <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">CC-BY</a> or <a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/">CC0</a> before submitting papers.</p>

<p>
